<br/>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        The <strong>IEEE International Symposium on Smart Electronic Systems (IEEE iSES 2025)</strong> invites proposals for <strong>Pre-Conference Tutorials</strong> that explore emerging trends and concepts in the design and applications of Smart Electronic Systems &amp; VLSI.
      </div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        We encourage tutorial proposals—both academic and industrial—that introduce novel topics or address recent technical trends in areas such as:
      </div>
<ul class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
<li>Home Automation</li>
<li>Wearables</li>
<li>Healthcare Systems</li>
<li>Smart Cities</li>
<li>Supply Chains</li>
<li>Smart Farming</li>
<li>Intelligent and Autonomous Systems</li>
<li>And others that are of interest to IEEE-iSES participant</li>
</ul>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        These tutorials aim to provide insights into emerging problems or cutting-edge solutions relevant to IEEE iSES participants.
      </div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-378e240f4a">
        Schedule:
      </div>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        Pre-Conference Tutorials will be conducted two days prior of <strong>December 13 and 14, 2025</strong>.
        Each tutorial is expected to be <strong>2–3 hours</strong> long.
      </div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-378e240f4a">
        Proposal Submission Guidelines:
      </div>
<div class="inline-7d27179924">
        Prepare a single PDF file (1–2 pages), using the template, that includes:
        <ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>A description of the session topic, format, and intended audience</li>
<li>List of speakers with biographical sketches</li>
<li>Presentation titles and brief abstracts</li>
</ul>
<ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>Submit your tutorial proposal through the <a href="https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/IEEEiSeS2025">Microsoft CMT</a> system.</li>
<li>The Microsoft CMT system will be used for reviewing the tutorials.</li>
<li>Detailed submission instructions will be provided upon proposal acceptance.</li>
</ul>
</div>
